description.p:
In extreme synthesis, the experimental work carried out by the present inventors has allowed to demonstrate that the e20 antibody fragment exhibits the following unexpected features:



    

it is generated in the course of a natural infection due to an HCV strain belonging to genotype 1b, but is able to bind to the glycoproteins from all of the known HCV genotypes (particularly genotypes 1a, 1b, 2a, 2b, 3, 4, 5 and 6) and as such is largely cross-reactive;

it possesses a particularly high neutralisation ability towards HCV genotypes 1a, 1b, 2a and 4, as measured by a neutralisation assay based on HCV pseudo-particles (HCVpp);

certain amino acid residues essential for the binding of e20 to HCV E2 glycoprotein are also essential in HCV infection, which suggests that mutants capable of escaping e20 binding are at the same time provided with a decreased replication ability.
